nsity)", "(used in calc_cross_sec)", "xraylib.CS_Phot()", "xraylib.CSb_Photo(Z,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.CS_Phot_CP()", "xraylib.CSb_Photo_CP(descriptor,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.CSb_Photo_CP(descriptor,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.CS_Rayl(Z,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.CSb_Rayl(Z,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.CS_Rayl_CP(descriptor,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.CSb_Rayl_CP(descriptor,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.CS_Compt(Z,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.CSb_Compt(Z,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.CS_Compt_CP(descriptor,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.CSb_Compt_CP(descriptor,1e-3*ienergy)", "xraylib.GetCompoundDataNISTList()", "xraylib.GetCompoundDataNISTByName(DESCRIPTOR)", "xraylib.GetCompoundDataNISTByIndex(DESCRIPTOR)", "TODO", "auxiliar methods", "there are not in xraylib, but accelerate the calculation"]}, {"name": "dabax.dabax_xraylib_decorator.DabaxXraylibDecorator.FiAndFii", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "Z", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "energy", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dabax.dabax_xraylib_decorator.DabaxXraylibDecorator.Crystal_F_0_F_H_F_H_bar_StructureFactor", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "crystal_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "energy_in_kev", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "millerH", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "millerK", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "millerL", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "debyeWaller", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rel_angle", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "dabax.common_tools.atomic_symbols", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["misc"]}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.atomic_names", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.atomic_number", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "symbol", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.parse_formula", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "formula", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.f0_xop", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "Z", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns the f0 value as stired in the f0_xop DABAX file:\n\nParametrization of f0 (the non-dispersive part of the atomic scttering factor) vs sin(theta/lambda).\nThis file contains a Waasmaier&Kirfel-like parametrization\nfor the f0 data evaluated by Kissel using modified relativistic form\nfactor [1]. For the fitting, model and the data error as in [2] are used.\nThe parametrization was calculating by fitting the\noriginal data in the RTAB database [1] (also in the DABAX file\nf0_mf_Kissel.dat) using the MPFIT IDL procedure of Markwardt\n(<http://cow.physics.wisc.edu/~craigm/idl/idl.html>) usind the\nfunction \\[2\\]:\n\n> > f0[k] = c + [SUM a_i\\*EXP(-b_i\\*(k^2)) ]\n> >\n> > : i=1,5\n>\n> where k = sin(theta) / lambda and c, a_i and b_i\n> are the coefficients tabulated in this file (in columns:\n> a1 a2 a3 a4 a5 c b1 b2 b3 b4 b5\n\nReferences\n[1] L. Kissel, Radiation physics and chemistry 59 (2000) 185-200\n\n> available at:\n> <http://www-phys.llnl.gov/Research/scattering/RTAB.html>\n\n[2] D. Waasmaier & A. Kirfel (Acta Cryst. (1995). A51, 416-413)\n\n> Remarks:\n> 1\\) This file contains data for only neutral atoms. For ionic states\n>\n> > other DABAX files (like f0_WaasKirf.dat) could be used.\n>\n> 2. The coefficients in this file are prepared for xop2.1 and are\n>    unpublished.\n>\n> 3. We created this file for being used as a default for XOP2.1. The\n>    reasons were two:\n>    i) It is more practical to use a parametrization rather than to use\n>\n>    > the direct data in file f0_mf.dat because of spped and storage\n>    > reasons.\n>\n>    2. The previous defaulty file for XOP 2.0 was f0_WaasKirf.dat, which\n>\n>    > contained a published parametrization [2], but the original data\n>    > is from the International Tables for X-ray Crystallography, vol C,\n>    > (1995) Edited by AJC Wilson, Kluwer Academic Press, table 6.1.1.3\n>    > which contains data from multiple origins (and references). We\n>    > prefer to use evaluated data in the same conditions for all elements\n>    > to keep some consistency in their origin.\n>    > Additionally, Kissel data for f1f2 and CrossSec are also used in XOP.\n\nColumn description: a1 a2 a3 a4 a5 c b1 b2 b3 b4 b5\n\n```\nparam Z\n\nthe atomic number\n\nreturn\n\nthe 11 coefficients for buiding f0\n```\n", "=======================================================================================================================", "f utilities", "=======================================================================================================================", "TODO: in future we will use xraylib, by now we use this."]}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.calculate_f0_from_f0coeff", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "f0coeff", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ratio", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["f0"]}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.f0_interpolate_coefficients", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "charge", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "charge_list", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "coefficient_list", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.__f0func", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "q", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a1", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a2", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a3", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a4", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a5", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a6", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a7", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a8", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a9", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.f0_xop_with_fractional_charge_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "Z", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.f0_xop_with_fractional_charge", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "Z", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "charge", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["    "]}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.bragg_metrictensor", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "c", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a1", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a2", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a3", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "RETURN_REAL_SPACE", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "RETURN_VOLUME", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "HKL", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns the metric tensor in the reciprocal space\n\n```\nparam a\n\nunit cell a\n\nparam b\n\nunit cell b\n\nparam c\n\nunit cell c\n\nparam a1\n\nunit cell alpha\n\nparam a2\n\nunit cell beta\n\nparam a3\n\nunit cell gamma\n\nparam RETURN_REAL_SPACE\n\nset to 1 for returning metric tensor in real space\n\nparam RETURN_VOLUME\n\nset to 1 to return the unit cell volume in Angstroms^3\n\nparam HKL\n\nif !=None, returns the d-spacing for the corresponding [H,K,L] reflection\n\nreturn\n\nthe returned value depends on the keywords used. If RETURN_REAL_SPACE=0,RETURN_VOLUME=0, and HKL=None\nthen retuns the metric tensor in reciprocal space.\n```\n", "=======================================================================================================================", "CRYSTAL UTILITIES", "======================================================================================================================="]}, {"name": "dabax.common_tools.lorentz", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "theta_bragg_deg", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "return_what", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This function returns the Lorentz factor, polarization factor (unpolarized beam), geometric factor,\nor a combination of them.\n\n```\nparam theta_bragg_deg\n\nBragg angle in degrees\n\nparam return_what\n\nA flag indicating the returned variable:\n0: (default) PolFac*lorentzFac\n1: PolFac\n2: lorentzFac\n3: geomFac\n\nreturn\n\na scalar value\n```\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}]}